  "commentary": "With SPX at 6990.42 sitting just below the massive 7000 gamma wall (17.1B), dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push above 7000 to hedge their long gamma exposure, creating strong resistance. The PIN regime with 116.5B total GEX suggests dealers will provide liquidity by selling rallies and buying dips, keeping price rangebound between the 6875 flip level and the stacked resistance around 7000-7100. Watch for mean reversion behavior with 7000 acting as a magnet - any break above faces heavy selling pressure from the layered gamma walls, while support builds around 6975 and strengthens significantly below 6875.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned around 7000 with limited upside due to massive dealer selling pressure.",
